# Memory Conventions

## Memory Files Are Append-Only
Files matching `memory/**/ROLLING.md`:
- **Never** delete existing entries
- **Never** reorder existing entries
- **Always** add new content at the END of the file
- One header per day: `## YYYY-MM-DD`
- 3-5 bullet points under each header: `- [observation]`

## Memory Directory Structure
```
memory/
  BIAS-TRACKER.md              ← 14-column daily table (special format)
  THESES.md                    ← Active portfolio theses
  macro/ROLLING.md
  bonds/ROLLING.md
  commodities/ROLLING.md
  forex/ROLLING.md
  crypto/ROLLING.md
  equity/ROLLING.md
  sectors/technology/ROLLING.md
  sectors/healthcare/ROLLING.md
  sectors/energy/ROLLING.md
  ... (11 sector subdirs)
  alternative-data/sentiment/ROLLING.md
  alternative-data/cta/ROLLING.md
  alternative-data/options/ROLLING.md
  alternative-data/politician/ROLLING.md
  institutional/flows/ROLLING.md
  institutional/hedge-fund/ROLLING.md
  international/ROLLING.md
```

## Memory Traversal
To search all memory files from shell scripts:
```bash
find memory/ -name "ROLLING.md"  # correct: finds all levels
memory/*/ROLLING.md              # WRONG: misses subdirectory levels
```

## BIAS-TRACKER.md Format
The daily bias table has 14 columns: Date, Macro, Bonds, USD, Gold, Oil, Crypto, Equities, Asia, Europe, EM, Sentiment, CTA, Conviction. Append a new row for each session — never edit past rows.

## Canonical research artifacts
Daily intelligence is **JSON-first** and lives in **Supabase** (`daily_snapshots`, `documents`, etc.). Markdown in the UI is derived. Do not treat gitignored scratch trees as source of truth.
